Cytobands

Alicia Pliego

#Gene Level copy number file from TCGA

Downloading the Gene level Copy number files from TCGA, I computed CIN in the following way: - gene CNV > 2.25 = Amp - gene CNV < 1.75 = Del

I have mapped cytobands to gene entrez ids using org.Hs.egMAP and using the cytobands I extract the gene level CIN which will be added at cytoband level for all the genes in that cytoband across all the different cases that we have from TCGA-SARC

Plots: 1- Overall boxplots: for each chromosome all the cytoband CIN per sarcoma type 1b - Overall heatmap: for each chromosome a heatmap with all the CIN per cytobands and annotation on the side for each sarcoma type 2- HRD boxplots: The same as before but separating HRDhigh/low 2b - is there any cytoband differentially expressed between HRD/low groups in particular? 3- Make enrichment in those cytobands :)
